Iavan Pijoos, News24Johannesburg - Thousands of EFF supporters, clad in their characteristic red T-shirts and berets, filled up the Boipatong Stadium, in the Vaal, ahead of the Youth Day celebrations on Friday.&nbsp; A sea of red made their way into the stadium while they were entertained with songs and slogans, including chants of "Long live EFF".&nbsp; EFF leader Julius Malema was expected to address the masses on Friday afternoon.&nbsp; About 50 buses were parked outside the stadium. Some youth dressed in their school uniform were also in attendance.#EFF supporters fill up Boipatong stadium ahead of their #YouthDay celebrations. @News24 pic.twitter.com/HqFaB4ikEv#EFF crowd at the #YouthDay2017 celebrations at the Boipatong stadium. @News24 pic.twitter.com/B3D54wVfdZ 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.